{
  "texts": [
    "So, they do not reflect the vocabulary or the order of acquisition of language by children.",
    "They are not a good guide to the bottom-up route by direct (DSG) and indirect (IVG) grounding that brought adults to where they could ground new words with the help of a dictionary.",
    "Nevertheless, there is a (mild) correlation between how \"deep\" a word is in the dictionary -from periphery to Kernel to MinSet: Deeper (content-) words are more frequent, and acquired younger.",
    "(Of course the function-words would be deeper too, had they needed grounding, but they don't; so they are not counted.",
    "Their use is learnable distributionally; but the referents and meanings of ungrounded content-words are not._."
  ]
}